    public interface TabSwitchedListener
extends java.util.EventListener
    An TabSwichedListener is a listener that is interested in the switch of the active tab in a GOAL window.
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      void tabSwitched(Tab tab)
      Invoked when the active tab in a GOAL window has been switched.

    • Method Detail

      • tabSwitched

        void tabSwitched(Tab tab)
        Invoked when the active tab in a GOAL window has been switched. Note that the new active tab may be null because there is no tab in the window.
        Parameters:
        tab - the new active tab
